-- Icahn said made offer for Reckson properties
-- 
-- Thu Dec 7, 2006 4:34pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/12/07/businesspro-reckson-icahn-dc-idUSN0727503820061207

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Billionaire investor Carl Icahn said 
on Thursday he made an offer to buy certain Westchester 
properties held by Reckson Associates Realty Corp. RA.N as 
part of its pending merger with SL Green Realty Corp ( SLG.N ). 

  Icahn said he made the offer to Reckson Chief Executive 
Scott Rechler to pay $125 million more to SL Green. He said he 
made the offer providing the money would go to Reckson 
shareholders.